name: BSU Communication Building
street: Campus Lane between Albertsons Library and tennis courts
directions: There are TWO gender-neutral, single, locking bathrooms—one on each floor. Go in main entrance. First floor bathroom is a hard left, past staircase, after you walk in main entrance. Second-floor bathroom is directly above the first-floor one, up the stairs. There is an elevator in the building (down the hall, by the soda and snack machines). Nice bathrooms.
comment: These used to be designated as faculty/staff bathrooms, but no longer.

name: Pig and Pastry
directions: Bishy Road is the queer centre of York!  Pig and Pastry cafe is at the end of the road furthest from York centre and is next to the car park.  It has a white shop front with a pride flag in the window.  The toilets are at the back, past the kitchen.
comment: This is a really lovely place for a coffee and a queer friendly meet up!

name: Piazza Building
directions: Heslington East Campus, University of York.  The revolving door entrance to the building is located opposite the Langwith / Ron Cooke Hub bus stop.  Go through the revolving door or accessible door and pass the reception on the left.  Turn left and the 'all genders welcome' toilets are on the right in about 10 - 15 metres.
comment: Floor to ceiling walls of the cubicles with sanitary bins in all cubicles.  Very spacious and safe!

name: Piazza Building
directions: Heslington East campus.  The Langwith College Bus Stop is directly outside the revolving door to enter the building.  On entering, proceed ahead past reception (on the left) and turn left.  The all genders welcome toilets are on the right.  Accessible toilets are located all the way throughout the building.
comment: Floor to ceiling walls and sanitary bins in each cubicle!

name: Joe & The Juice
directions: Straight through the dining section from the front door on the left hand side. Rly great private single stall, ambiance a plus.

name: Baker Free Library
directions: Go through the two sets of doors (unlocked during library hours) then on your immediate left you will find the bathroom.
comment: It is a single room (or stall) bathroom that is gender neutral. It is a free public library so you don't have to pretend to be a costumer.
